OL,3,CPolice apologise after 'explosive'
OL,4,Creport into treatment of women in
OL,5,Ccustody
OL,7,FDame Vera set out recommendations on
OL,8,Fdomestic abuse, better custody
OL,9,Fprovision especially for women,
OL,10,Fimproved risk assessment and more
OL,11,Fhumane and dignified treatment of all
OL,12,Fdetainees, a lay presence in police
OL,13,Fcustody and also on arrests.
OL,15,FAssistant Chief Constable Tom Harding,
OL,16,Fdirector of operational standards at
OL,17,Fthe College of Policing, said the
OL,18,Freport makes for "difficult but
OL,19,Fnecessary reading".
OL,26,@zD@ROU{D@RO]
